OL,5,Cthroats'
OL,7,FMr Bowden claimed Mr Rawle gave him
OL,8,Fincorrect advice about a faulty pipe
OL,9,Fand that Mr Rawle became angry.
OL,11,F"It was appalling," Mr Bowden said.
OL,12,F"He was almost incoherent, the rage he
OL,13,Fdisplayed was just unrealistic given
OL,14,Fthe circumstances.
OL,16,F"He was spitting, he seemed out of
OL,17,Fcontrol, and I think it was then that
OL,18,Fhe suddenly turned and urinated on our
OL,19,Fproperty."
