OL,5,Cthroats'
OL,7,FMr Priddle said he heard a woman's
OL,8,Fvoice shouting for help in
OL,9,F"considerable distress".
OL,11,F"She shouted 'help' repeatedly and
OL,12,F'get away from me you effing bastard'
OL,13,Fat one point."
OL,15,FMr Priddle said the voice sounded
OL,16,F"frantic" and "distressed". "I thought
OL,17,Fsomebody was in trouble and was in
OL,18,Fneed of help," he added.
